Eight 3.3V general-purpose digital input pins of MAX3421E. They are used primarily to interface with buttons, rotary encoders and such. GPIN pins can also be programmed as a source of MAX3421E interrupt.
Eight 3.3V general-purpose digital output pins of MAX3421E.
They are not used by the shield and provided only for convenience.
They are not used by the shield and provided only for convenience.
The shield in its default configuration uses pins 9 and 10 for INT and SS
interface signals. INT and SS signals can be re-assigned to other pins;
If default SS (D10) pin is occupied by other applications and need to be re-wired, it can be placed to any vacant pin.
MAX3421E interrupt pin. If necessary, INT can be re-wired from this pin using extra pad and jumper

It is currently not used. It can be used as a second interrupt pin of MAX3421E.
It can be used to provide 5V to VBUS. By default, VBUS is connected to 3.3V; certain USB devices may have issues with this.
It is used by the shield to send/receive data using SPI interface. SCK, MOSI, MISO and RESET signals from this connector are used.
Arduino RESET pin. Pulling it low will reset MAX3421E into initial power-on
